[32m│[0m hexadecimal strings, which suggests SHA-256 hashing (256 bits = 64 hex       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m chars). This is consistent with the Flask application using a hash-based     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m session mechanism.                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **No Username Enumeration**: The application properly returns the same    [32m│[0m
